---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import { siteFromHost } from '../../content';
const site = siteFromHost();
const path = '/alternatives/postscript-alternative';
const title = 'Best Postscript Alternatives for Shopify in 2026';
const desc = 'Compare Postscript alternatives for Shopify by SMS focus, email lifecycle depth, consent governance, ecommerce events, pricing, and team fit.';
const tools = [
  { name: 'Attentive', best: 'Brands with a dedicated SMS growth program', price: 'Verify current messaging and contract pricing', pros: 'SMS-focused segmentation, capture, and campaign operations', cons: 'May be more platform than a small store needs', source: 'https://www.attentive.com/pricing' },
  { name: 'Klaviyo', best: 'Stores coordinating SMS with detailed email and product behavior', price: 'Verify current contact and channel pricing', pros: 'Deep commerce events across email and SMS', cons: 'Requires careful consent and frequency governance', source: 'https://www.klaviyo.com/pricing' },
  { name: 'Omnisend', best: 'SMB stores wanting accessible email and SMS journeys', price: 'Verify current contact and channel pricing', pros: 'Fast multichannel ecommerce setup', cons: 'Message economics and overlap need monitoring', source: 'https://www.omnisend.com/pricing/' },
  { name: 'Brevo', best: 'Teams combining SMS with email and transactional messaging', price: 'Verify current send, contact, and channel pricing', pros: 'Broad channel coverage', cons: 'Shopify-specific SMS and lifecycle modeling may need testing', source: 'https://www.brevo.com/pricing/' },
  { name: 'Sequenzy', best: 'Teams that want email lifecycle ownership beside a specialist SMS tool', price: 'Verify current plan and integration coverage', pros: 'Focused sequences and clear channel boundaries', cons: 'Not a drop-in SMS replacement; validate handoff requirements', source: 'https://sequenzy.io/' },
];
const faqs = [
  { question: 'Why leave Postscript?', answer: 'A store may need deeper email lifecycle automation, richer product-event segmentation, a different SMS operating model, or clearer separation between SMS urgency and email education.' },
  { question: 'Should email and SMS be in one platform?', answer: 'Not always. One platform can simplify suppression, but specialists can be better when the team has clear ownership and a shared collision calendar.' },
  { question: 'What must be checked before migrating SMS?', answer: 'Consent source and timestamps, quiet hours, opt-out behavior, phone-number portability, message templates, audience exclusions, and the handoff between SMS and email.' },
];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />
  <main class="container py-14 md:py-20">
    <nav class="mb-8 text-sm"><a class="link" href="/alternatives">Alternatives hub</a><span class="mx-2 text-slate-400">/</span><span class="text-slate-400">Postscript</span></nav>
    <header class="max-w-4xl"><span class="badge">Shopify SMS and lifecycle guide</span><h1 class="hero-title mt-5">{title}</h1><p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-xl text-cyan-100">Postscript alternatives should be evaluated as a channel-ownership decision. SMS is scarce, consent-sensitive, and urgent; email often has a different job in the same customer journey.</p><p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-slate-300">Choose a replacement based on whether you are replacing SMS, consolidating channels, or adding a stronger email lifecycle layer.</p></header>
    <section class="mt-12 max-w-5xl overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08]"><table class="w-full text-left"><thead><tr><th>Platform</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Pros</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{tools.map((tool, i) => <tr class={i === 0 ? 'highlight-row' : ''}><td class="font-semibold text-white">{tool.name}</td><td>{tool.best}</td><td>{tool.pros}</td><td>{tool.cons}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table></section>
    <section class="prose-shopify mt-14 max-w-4xl">
      <h2>Separate urgency from education</h2><p>An SMS cart reminder, a replenishment text, and a product-education email should not compete for the same attention window. Before migrating, map the customer states and assign each channel a job. Then document the collision rules that prevent a discount from arriving three times.</p><p>SMS migration also carries consent and operational risk. Preserve opt-in evidence, quiet-hour rules, opt-out handling, and suppression state. A successful email test does not prove that an SMS migration is compliant or commercially safe.</p>
      <h2>Platform notes</h2>{tools.map((tool, i) => <section><h3>{i + 1}. {tool.name}</h3><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {tool.best}. <strong>Pros:</strong> {tool.pros}. <strong>Cons:</strong> {tool.cons}. <strong>Pricing:</strong> {tool.price}. Read the <a href={tool.source} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">official source</a> and include message volume, contacts, seats, consent tooling, and migration work.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Consent test</th><td>Can the team prove opt-in source, honor opt-out, enforce quiet hours, and preserve exclusions?</td></tr><tr><th>Collision test</th><td>Can the platform or operating process suppress an SMS when the same offer or message was already sent by email?</td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}
      <h2>Migration checklist</h2><ol><li>Export phone consent, timestamps, source, quiet-hour policy, opt-outs, segments, templates, and live flows.</li><li>Map Shopify product, cart, order, subscription, and customer events to each channel.</li><li>Define one owner for SMS compliance and one owner for cross-channel suppression.</li><li>Test cart, post-purchase, replenishment, and winback paths with a real order and opt-out case.</li><li>Launch in stages and measure incremental orders, margin, opt-outs, complaints, and email collisions.</li></ol>
      <h2>Verdict</h2><p>Choose Attentive for a dedicated SMS growth operation, Klaviyo for deep email-plus-SMS commerce behavior, Omnisend for accessible multichannel workflows, Brevo for broader messaging, and Sequenzy when email lifecycle should be owned separately from a specialist SMS channel. Do not consolidate channels unless the team can preserve clear consent and suppression ownership.</p>
    </section>
    <FaqSection faqs={faqs} />
    <p class="mt-12 text-slate-300">Continue with the <a class="link" href="/apps">app profiles</a>, <a class="link" href="/use-cases">use cases</a>, and <a class="link" href="/guides">operator guides</a>.</p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
